{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863856186,"sessionID":"ses_286455755ffeil0ob5fx7cp3eX","part":{"id":"prt_d79bbf63e001QIg0UIYNveWDCE","messageID":"msg_d79bbdfd9001OrveSMyTYtU7sP","sessionID":"ses_286455755ffeil0ob5fx7cp3eX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_950937ea097448bfbdc5e544","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `sdk-python`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** <!-- TODO: Reference base specs -->\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: <!-- TODO: Define requirements in Given/When/Then format -->\n13: \n14: ## File Changes\n15: \n16: | Action | File | Description |\n17: |--------|------|-------------|\n18: | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> |\n\n(End of file - total 18 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** <!-- TODO: Reference base specs -->\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n<!-- TODO: Define requirements in Given/When/Then format -->\n\n## File Changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775863856176,"end":1775863856184}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775863856637,"sessionID":"ses_286455755ffeil0ob5fx7cp3eX","part":{"id":"prt_d79bbfded001Y3UHv0COO92KKV","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79bbdfd9001OrveSMyTYtU7sP","sessionID":"ses_286455755ffeil0ob5fx7cp3eX","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":32553,"input":32414,"output":80,"reasoning":59,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.009175753}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775863860701,"sessionID":"ses_286455755ffeil0ob5fx7cp3eX","part":{"id":"prt_d79bc0dda001TaOETW9Fq31cZK","messageID":"msg_d79bbfe1f001H6MA5DjTisKj72","sessionID":"ses_286455755ffeil0ob5fx7cp3eX","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863931400,"sessionID":"ses_286455755ffeil0ob5fx7cp3eX","part":{"id":"prt_d79bc15dd001Hn1pPVm8jcoiwZ","messageID":"msg_d79bbfe1f001H6MA5DjTisKj72","sessionID":"ses_286455755ffeil0ob5fx7cp3eX","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_91f564a149904e0ea148dbdd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-027: SDK CodeInterpreterClient — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient Initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct a `CodeInterpreterClient` that resolves configuration from arguments and environment variables, then initializes internal clients for control plane and data plane communication.\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor with all defaults\n- **GIVEN** no arguments are passed to `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__`\n- **WHEN** the environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **THEN** the client SHALL initialize with `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`, and `router_url` from the environment\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL required\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n\n#### Scenario: Custom configuration\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is constructed with explicit `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, and `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** the constructor completes\n- **THEN** all instance fields (`name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `router_url`, `session_id`) SHALL be set to the provided values, and `cp_client` SHALL be initialized with the control plane configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from service account file\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided and `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL read the token via `read_token_from_file` and set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header on the session\n\n#### Scenario: Auth token from service account file missing\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided and the SA token file does not exist\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `read_token_from_file` SHALL return `\"\"` and no `Authorization` header SHALL be set\n\n### Requirement: Session Lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL manage Code Interpreter sessions through creation, reuse, and deletion, with proper cleanup on context manager exit.\n\n#### Scenario: Session creation on init\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided to the constructor\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `cp_client.create_session(name, namespace, ttl=ttl)` and store the returned session ID\n\n#### Scenario: Session reuse\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is provided to the constructor\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL NOT call `create_session` and SHALL use the provided `session_id` for data plane initialization\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager entry\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in a `with` statement\n- **WHEN** `__enter__` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `self`\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit with normal flow\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager and the block completes without exception\n- **WHEN** `__exit__` is called with `exc_type=None`\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `stop()` to clean up resources\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager and an exception occurs in the block\n- **WHEN** `__exit__` is called with exception info\n- **THEN** it SHALL call `stop()` and SHALL NOT suppress the exception (return `None` or `False`)\n\n#### Scenario: Stop method cleanup\n- **GIVEN** `stop()` is called on a client with an active session\n- **WHEN** `stop()` executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL close the data plane client, delete the control plane session if `session_id` is set, and close the control plane client session\n\n#### Scenario: Stop method idempotency\n- **GIVEN** `stop()` is called multiple times\n- **WHEN** subsequent calls execute\n- **THEN** they SHALL NOT raise errors (safe to call repeatedly)\n\n### Requirement: Data Plane Initialization\n\nThe system SHALL initialize the `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` after session creation, with proper error handling and cleanup on failure.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful data plane init\n- **GIVEN** a valid `session_id` is available\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, and `cr_name=name`, and assign it to `self.dp_client`\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise the exception\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init with existing session\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was provided to the constructor\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL initialize the data plane client without attempting to delete any session on failure\n\n### Requirement: Command Execution\n\nThe system SHALL execute commands in the Code Interpreter session via the data plane API, with proper timeout handling and error reporting.\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command success\n- **GIVEN** a valid session and data plane client\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL POST to `api/execute` with body `{\"command\": [\"echo hello\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` and return the stdout from the response\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with custom timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with `timeout=30.0`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `\"timeout\": \"30s\"` and the HTTP read timeout SHALL be `32.0` seconds (timeout + 2.0 buffer)\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command with default timeout\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with `timeout=None`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the effective timeout SHALL default to `120` seconds, body SHALL include `\"timeout\": \"120s\"`, and HTTP read timeout SHALL be `122.0` seconds\n\n#### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n- **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command` from the response\n\n#### Scenario: Command as list\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with a list `[\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('hi')\"]`\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the body SHALL include `\"command\": [\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('hi')\"]`\n\n### Requirement: Code Execution\n\nThe system SHALL execute code snippets by writing them to temporary files and running the appropriate interpreter.\n\n#### Scenario: Python code execution\n- **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language=\"python\"` and some code\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n\n#### Scenario: Python3 language alias\n- **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language=\"python3\"`\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL treat it as Python and write a `.py` file\n\n#### Scenario: Py language alias\n- **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language=\"py\"`\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL treat it as Python and write a `.py` file\n\n#### Scenario: Unsupported language\n- **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with an unsupported `language`\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating the language is not supported\n\n### Requirement: File Operations\n\nThe system SHALL provide file upload, download, write, and listing operations through the data plane API.\n\n#### Scenario: Write file\n- **GIVEN** `write_file` is called with `content` and `remote_path`\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL POST to `api/files` with JSON body `{\"path\": remote_path, \"content\": <base64-encoded>, \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: Upload file\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file` is called with `local_path` and `remote_path`\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL POST multipart to `api/files` with `files={'file': ...}` and `data={'path': remote_path, 'mode': '0644'}`, including `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n\n#### Scenario: Download file\n- **GIVEN** `download_file` is called with `remote_path` and `local_path`\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL GET `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True` (where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) and write the response content to `local_path`\n\n#### Scenario: List files\n- **GIVEN** `list_files` is called with `path=\".\"`\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL GET `api/files` with query parameter `path=.` and return the response\n\n#### Scenario: List files with custom path\n- **GIVEN** `list_files` is called with `path=\"/tmp\"`\n- **WHEN** the method executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL GET `api/files` with query parameter `path=/tmp`\n\n### Requirement: HTTP Client Configuration\n\nThe system SHALL configure HTTP clients with appropriate connection pooling, timeouts, and headers for both control plane and data plane communication.\n\n#### Scenario: Control plane session configuration\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL have `HTTPAdapter` mounted for `http://` and `https://` with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`, and default headers `Content-Type: application/json`\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane session configuration\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the session is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL have `HTTPAdapter` mounted with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`, and default header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane base URL construction\n- **GIVEN** `base_url` is not provided to `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL construct `base_url` via `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane explicit base URL\n- **GIVEN** `base_url` is explicitly provided to `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `base_url` directly without constructing from `router_url`\n\n### Requirement: Timeout Defaults\n\nThe system SHALL apply consistent timeout defaults across all HTTP operations, with per-call override support.\n\n#### Scenario: Control plane default timeouts\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout arguments\n- **WHEN** any request is made\n- **THEN** the timeout tuple SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane default timeouts\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout arguments\n- **WHEN** any request is made\n- **THEN** the timeout tuple SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` unless overridden per-call\n\n#### Scenario: Execute command timeout buffer\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with a numeric `timeout` value\n- **WHEN** the HTTP request is made\n- **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `timeout + 2.0` seconds to prevent premature `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124\n\n### Requirement: Exception Hierarchy\n\nThe system SHALL define and use a consistent exception hierarchy for error handling.\n\n#### Scenario: CommandExecutionError attributes\n- **GIVEN** a command fails with non-zero exit code\n- **WHEN** `CommandExecutionError` is raised\n- **THEN** it SHALL have attributes `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`, and the message SHALL include `\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCubeError base class\n- **GIVEN** `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, or `DataPlaneError` is raised\n- **WHEN** caught as `AgentCubeError`\n- **THEN** it SHALL be catchable since all are subclasses of `AgentCubeError`\n\n#### Scenario: SessionError definition\n- **GIVEN** `SessionError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n- **WHEN** imported\n- **THEN** it SHALL be a subclass of `AgentCubeError` with docstring `\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"`\n\n#### Scenario: DataPlaneError definition\n- **GIVEN** `DataPlaneError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n- **WHEN** imported\n- **THEN** it SHALL be a subclass of `AgentCubeError` with docstring `\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"`\n\n### Requirement: Logging\n\nThe system SHALL provide configurable logging for debugging and operational visibility.\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose logging enabled\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is constructed with `verbose=True`\n- **WHEN** operations are performed\n- **THEN** the logger SHALL output debug-level messages\n\n#### Scenario: Default logging level\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is constructed with `verbose=False` (default)\n- **WHEN** operations are performed\n- **THEN** the logger SHALL output at `INFO` level or higher\n\n### Requirement: Public API Surface\n\nThe system SHALL export only the intended public classes from the package.\n\n#### Scenario: Root package exports\n- **GIVEN** `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient`\n- **WHEN** the import succeeds\n- **THEN** both classes SHALL be accessible and `agentcube.__all__` SHALL contain exactly `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Clients submodule exports\n- **GIVEN** `from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n- **WHEN** the import succeeds\n- **THEN** all three classes SHALL be accessible and `agentcube.clients.__all__` SHALL contain exactly `[\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n\n## File Changes\n\n| Action | File | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| Create | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports for `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` |\n| Create | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` class with context manager support |\n| Create | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` class |\n| Create | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`) |\n| Create | `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-exports for internal client classes |\n| Create | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` for Workload Manager API |\n| Create | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` for Router data plane API |\n| Create | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Agent Runtime data plane |\n| Create | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` helper with HTTPAdapter mounting |\n| Create | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` helper |\n| Create | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` helper |\n| Create | `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty module marker |\n| Create | `pyproject.toml` | Package configuration with dependencies (`requests`, `PyJWT`, `cryptography`) |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775863931382,"end":1775863931397}}}}
